<statement>
<p>If a right triangle has legs of length <m>\displaystyle{a}={15}</m> and <m>\displaystyle{b}={18}</m>, what are the angles in degrees</p>
<p>
  opposite from side of length <m>\displaystyle{a}={15}</m>: <m>\displaystyle{A}\approx</m> <input type="text" style="width:4.6ch" name="qn1000" id="qn1000" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 1 of 2" class="text"/><circumflex/><m>\displaystyle\circ</m> </p>
<p>
  opposite from side of length <m>\displaystyle{b}={18}</m>: <m>\displaystyle{B}\approx</m> <input type="text" style="width:4.6ch" name="qn1001" id="qn1001" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 2 of 2" class="text"/><circumflex/><m>\displaystyle\circ</m> </p>
<p>Round to units.</p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>40</li><li>50</li></ul></p><p>For angle <m>\displaystyle{A}</m> the opposite side has length <m>\displaystyle{a}={15}</m> and the adjacent side has length <m>\displaystyle{b}={18}</m>. The angle is therefore</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{A}={\arctan{{\left(\frac{{15}}{{18}}\right)}}}\approx{39.805571092265}^{\circ}\approx{40}^{\circ}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle <m>\displaystyle{B}</m> the opposite side has length <m>\displaystyle{b}={18}</m> and the adjacent side has length <m>\displaystyle{a}={15}</m>. The angle is therefore</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={\arctan{{\left(\frac{{18}}{{15}}\right)}}}\approx{50.194428907735}^{\circ}\approx{50}^{\circ}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>